      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The current administration's actions have made the decline of unionization worse by implementing policies that weaken labor unions and make it harder for workers to organize. For example, the \"Right to Work\" laws, which have been championed by the administration, allow workers to opt-out of paying union dues, effectively starving unions of revenue and making it harder for them to function. Additionally, the administration's \"Persuader Rule\" repeal, which was finalized in 2020, allows employers to hire outside \"persuaders\" to intimidate and discourage workers from organizing, further undermining the labor movement.",
